      <section eId="sec_2100">
        <num>2100</num>
        <heading>Communicable diseases; local boards of health and health officers; powers and duties</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2100__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>provide for care and isolation of cases of communicable disease in\na hospital or elsewhere when necessary for protection of the public\nhealth and,\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2100__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>subject to the provisions of the sanitary code, prohibit and\nprevent all intercourse and communication with or use of infected\npremises, places and things, and require, and if necessary, provide the\nmeans for the thorough purification and cleansing of the same before\ngeneral intercourse with the same or use thereof shall be allowed.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
